# Renderer conventions

## Stack

- **Vue 2.7** + **Vuex 3** + **Vue Router 3** + **Element UI 2** + **vue-i18n 8**
- Entry: [app/renderer/js/app.js](app/renderer/js/app.js) → bundled to `build/app.js`

## IPC from components

Access via `this.$ipc` (set in app.js):

```javascript
const { body } = await this.$ipc.request('tasks/list', { projectId });
```

Match route names to handlers in `app/src/routes/`. Add both sides when introducing a new endpoint.

## State management

- Global state: [app/renderer/js/storage/store.js](app/renderer/js/storage/store.js) (Vuex)
- Prefer Vuex actions for IPC calls and shared state; keep components thin
- Routes: [app/renderer/js/router/routes.js](app/renderer/js/router/routes.js)

## Components

- Layout: `app/renderer/js/components/`
- User area: `components/user/` (tasks, settings, intervals, offline sync)
- Use Element UI (`el-button`, `el-row`, etc.) — match existing markup style
- User-visible strings: `$t('key')` — add keys to `app/src/translations/en.json` and `ru.json`

## Styles

- Global SCSS: [app/renderer/scss/app.scss](app/renderer/scss/app.scss) and `imports/`
- Component-scoped styles in `.vue` files when needed
- Rebuild styles: `yarn build-development`

## Sentry

Initialized in app.js from query param injected by main process. Do not hardcode DSN in renderer.
